 <body>
  <ol>
   <li><p>From the advanced menu, via the Adobe Campaign logo, select <strong>Profiles &amp; audiences &gt; Profiles</strong>.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Complete or create profiles, then complete the new <strong>Promo code</strong> field.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/schema_extension_UC3.png" title="" /></li>
   <li><p>Select <strong>Profiles &amp; Audiences &gt; Test profiles</strong> in the navigation pane.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Complete or create a new test profile, then complete the new <strong>Promo code</strong> field.</p> <img alt="" captionBottom="" imageRotate="0" src="assets/schema_extension_UC4.png" title="" /></li>
   <li><p>Create a <strong>new email</strong> in a marketing campaign.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Create an <strong>Audience</strong> from a <strong>simple rule</strong>: <strong>Promo code is not empty</strong>. This rule is valid for the main target as well as for the test profiles.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Insert the <strong>Promo code</strong> field into the email content. </p> </li>
   <li><p>Send the email to the test profiles selected by the audience.</p> </li>
   <li><p>Send the email to the profiles selected by the audience.</p> </li>
  </ol>
  <p>The values of the <strong>Promo code</strong> personalized field are contextualized by profile type when the email is sent.</p> 
